      <description>Based on what you posted, which looks to be basically correct, AoW *was* beaten pre-luclin, so you were incorrect.&amp;nbsp; i.e. AoW was beaten, w/o charm giants, and without AeT.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Also, my whole point was that the tank, unless he was a fool, wouldn't disc forti because it would blow his def... obviously, a rogue/bard/ranger/etc would use his riposte/avoidance disc.&amp;nbsp; That wasn't really up for debate.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;AoW definitely involved some luck, but I liked that.&amp;nbsp; It also involved a lot of fast reflexes... when your tank died cause the AoW decided to flurry a lot, if your clerics' reaction times were half a second slower than ideal, the tank died... with Vish, I've seen us win with the tank shouting for 20s that he's the MT, and ppl are too busy chatting on skype or whatever to pay attention.&amp;nbsp; It's so easy.&amp;nbsp; Sure, Vish was challenging to figure out, to learn what each mob did, how to use the clouds, how to handle the dt ae, why not to kill those stupid mobs with the stun/knockback, etc... but once you learn all that, it's trivial, and easily repeated, and requires no skill.&amp;nbsp; You'd have to be a moron to miss the deathtouches with audio triggers now.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;AoW was exciting because the outcome wasn't guaranteed.&amp;nbsp; Vish is boring, because you always win.&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
