      <description>"Fortitude was available from Kunark on, so could be used against AoW,&#xD;
with the real difficulty in tank transitions being in not having AET&#xD;
when before Luclin...opps, wait, guilds did not start beating AoW till&#xD;
Luclin, so that ends that difficulty too."&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Lol I knew you'd say that, obviously someone who didn't play a tank class back in Velious.&amp;nbsp; You couldn't use forti on aow because it counted as a disc, and then you couldn't use defensive, and you couldn't survive w/o defensive.&amp;nbsp; With the new disc system, you can use forti, then as soon as it drops, pop defensive.&amp;nbsp; So no, you could not use forti on AoW as you can today.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Also, you're wrong about when AoW was killed.&amp;nbsp; He was killed on 2 servers during Velious, Legacy of Steel/Shock of Swords did him together on Nameless, and FoH did him on Veeshan.&amp;nbsp; They didn't have AeT.&amp;nbsp; Also, on this new server, we will probably have to do him w/o AeT, since he'll probably be part of the process of unlocking luclin.&amp;nbsp; The devs at the summit, when they explained the idea of progression servers unlocking, used the example of the aow unlocking Luclin, so it's a good bet.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I already agreed with you that some classes, especially random_dps_class_04, has to pay more attention on vish than on aow.&amp;nbsp; A rogue still had to pay attention though.&amp;nbsp; They had to watch the tank switches, turn off attack between them, control aggro, etc... but if they **SMURF**ed up, they just died, they didn't wipe the guild (although turning the aow then made half the guild riposte him).&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;However, the guild as a whole, even after beating aow once, was still quite likely to lose again.&amp;nbsp; That's not true of vish.&amp;nbsp; Once you get the strat down, you can just win every time.&amp;nbsp; AoW, no matter how good your strat... it was always touch and go.&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
