      <description>I agree that newer encounters often require more equivalent levels of attention from all players across the board, like the dt in vish.&amp;nbsp; However, I think that it's much easier on the guild as a whole, in that once we figured vish out, we rarely lost it.&amp;nbsp; AoW wasn't like that.&amp;nbsp; On Vish, we just chaos chain on the main tank.&amp;nbsp; If it's 5s or even 10s sometimes between heals, the tank might live.&amp;nbsp; With AoW, if that cheal is off by half a second, the tank is dead.&amp;nbsp; In fact, even if the cheal is dead on, once per second, the tank might be dead if aow gets a good round.&amp;nbsp; When a tank splatted, the clerics had to react immediately and much faster than on Vish.&amp;nbsp; Now you just /disc fortitude to give yourself 10-12s or so plus the amount of time you already had.&amp;nbsp; You can easily survive 20s without a heal if you're a halfway decent tank.&amp;nbsp; The AoW could eat an uber velious tank in 1 round if unlucky, 2 if lucky.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;That kind of incredibly challenging encounter is gone from EQ.&amp;nbsp; The kind where, no matter how well you knew the encounter, no matter how good your strats, there was a good chance you'd lose anyways.&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
