    <item>
      <title>Re: One last glimpse of EQ's original magic</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Progression&amp;message.id=17009#M17009</link>
      <description>In a way, newer style raids are easier, and in way, they are harder.&amp;nbsp; The style of raids changed.&amp;nbsp; They used to be about reflexes, reacting time, gear quality, and speed in mobilization.&amp;nbsp; Now they are about figuring out a gimmick or puzzle.&amp;nbsp; The older fights didn't really get easier with time except in that your gear got better.&amp;nbsp; The new fights are very hard at first, but once you figure out the trick, they become immediately trivial.&amp;nbsp; Once you learn how to win the fight, you can do it again and again and again, without a very impressive raid force, and without much skill.&amp;nbsp; In the old days, every time you engaged the AoW, you weren't sure if you were going to win, until gear got to the point where it gave you wiggle room if you screwed up.&amp;nbsp; IMO, the older style was more fun, because it wasn't so boring to farm mobs when each time it was challenging.&amp;nbsp; Some people prefer the newer style raids, where it's just about figuring out a puzzle.&amp;nbsp; It's just a matter of preference.&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
      <pubDate>Sat, 03 Jun 2006 20:18:06 GMT</pubDate>
